-- Erdogan Changes Security Chief, Bodyguards, Hurriyet Reports
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2012-09-25T05:36:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/erdogan-changes-security-chief-bodyguards-hurriyet-reports.html
Turkish Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan  has appointed a new security chief and his bodyguards
have been changed,  Hurriyet newspaper said , without saying where
it got the information.  The appointment of Ramazan Bal to take charge of protecting
Erdogan has triggered the changes in five police squads in
Ankara and Istanbul, the Istanbul-based paper said. The changes
will affect more than 300 officers who protect Erdogan at all
times, Hurriyet said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcan Hacaoglu in Ankara at 
 shacaoglu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
